osphate buffer as 2 or 3 times the dry weight of sample depending on the quantity of sediment sampled and the water content. You will apply the same ratio for all samples of a same study. It is important to take care to not sample too much sediments to be able to add the phosphate buffer in the 50 ml falcon and avoid overflowing.<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Add the right quantities of NaH2PO4 and NA2HPO4 in the DNA-free water (To prepare<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\"><a href=\"#\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\"> <\/span><\/a><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">  of phosphate buffer: add <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\"><a href=\"#\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\"> <\/span><\/a><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\"> of NaH2PO4 powder and <\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\"><a href=\"#\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\"> <\/span><\/a><\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">of NA2HPO4 powder)\u00a0<\/li><li style = \"counter-reset:ol0;\">Mix until the total dissolution of the phosphate powder. Please be sure that the phosphate powder is completely dissoluted (i.e. no powder emains in the bottle)<\/li><\/ol><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Add the right quantities of NaH2PO4 and NA2HPO4 in the DNA-free water (To prepare<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">  of phosphate buffer: add <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> of NaH2PO4 powder and <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">of NA2HPO4 powder)\u00a0<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><ol style = \"list-style-type: decimal;\"><\/ol><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">If you have, put in the UV box for <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> \u00a0<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"A15B22A0734A11EA84E4C96E9A0B1769","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":1,"unit":"L","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":